bib.title: The 23Na(D,A)21Ne Reaction For Deuteron Energies Of2.3-4.0 Mev.

free_txt: with the energy resolution for alpha particles no worse
than 20 keV in the working area of 5-10 MeV were used.
A layer of NaBr (~ 200 mu-g/cm2 thick) evaporated on
a thin coal backing (30 mu-g/cm2) was used as a target.
